cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category since the paper presents an algorithmic solution to a graph problem. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category since the paper analyzes the time complexity of the algorithm and compares it to previous results. 

cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category since the paper deals with a graph problem that involves finding an independent set of vertices. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category since the paper deals with a combinatorial problem on graphs. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible since the paper deals with a problem that could be relevant to certain AI applications involving graphs.
